        <comment xml:lang="en">Calculation.  This data was calculated from the amount of butanediol in the treated waste water assuming a carbon conversion of 96% for COD.  The worst case scenario TOC=DOC was used.  
It is assumed that the manufacturing plants are located in an urban/industrial area and consequently the emissions are categorised as emanating in a high population density area.
Water emissions are assumed to be emitted into rivers.</comment>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">TOC</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">total organic carbon</synonym>
